Two Pointer Algorithm (Java Notes)


What is Two Pointer Algorithm?

The Two Pointer Algorithm uses two indices (pointers) to solve problems efficiently on arrays or strings.

Instead of using nested loops (O(n²)), it often solves problems in O(n) time.

When to Use?

Use the Two Pointer technique when:

Array is sorted.
Need to find a pair of elements.
Need to remove duplicates.
Need to reverse an array or string.
Need to check palindrome.


Types of Two Pointers

1. Opposite Direction
One pointer starts from the beginning (left).
Another pointer starts from the end (right).

Example:

Array:
1 2 3 4 5 6

L         R


2. Same Direction (Fast & Slow Pointer)
Both pointers start from the beginning.
One moves faster than the other.

Example:

Slow -> 1 2 3 4 5
Fast -> 1 2 3 4 5